name: Power Rack
des: Power rack, also known as full rack is a massive square-like piece of equipment, which can be used for various exercise, including squats, bench presses, pull-ups and some of them.

name: Squat Rack
des: Half rack is basically one half of a power rack. It does not take a lot of space (in comparison to a full rack), it’s usually cheaper, but you can’t do.

name: Cable Crossover Machine
des: You can usually find a good cable cross-over machine in your local gym. From my personal experience.

name: Power Tower
des: Power towers are quite accessible these days, from various manufacturers in various quality. You can also get a commercially-graded one, which is of course more expensive.

name: Hammer Strength Machine
des: In most well-equipment public gyms, you can come across a hammer strength machine. This particular piece of equipment uses iso-lateral technology.

name: Chest Press Machine
des: The machine works the same pectoral muscles as a bench press, although the design is a bit different. You are actually pushing in front of you two mechanical.
